"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-12-olympics-nigerian-only-participated-in-sports-that-dont-need-investment-seun-kuti\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Famous singer, Seun Kuti has blasted the Nigerian government for not investing in sports.  In a viral video on social media, Seun reacted to team Nigeria's poor performance at the just concluded 2024 Olympics in Paris.  While highlighting the 2024 Olympics, the singer revealed that Nigeria only participated in sporting events that do not require investment.  \\\"I watched the Olympic games. look at how poorly we performed. How many sports are we competing in? I saw that it was only sports that did not need investment that Nigerians participated in. We only did sports that needed minimum investment.  \\\"You know, to play football, you need a ball, post and net and in some places, boys would use slippers to create a goalpost. But in sports that need things like rackets, basketball courts, rims and nets where you can not easily improvise, we were not there. We competed in track and field events because it is easy to do running. But we are never in sports that need equipment.  \\\"Nigerians know all these sports and bet on them so how much would it take to create a good league and gift the winners 25 million dollars? Let there be a minimum of a million dollars per year, after all, this is what boys are earning in Europe.  \\\"Nigerians are unable to enjoy their children's talents, all our big superstars. Which other shows do they play in Nigeria? I was watching the Olympics and I saw a lot of people with Nigerian sounding names doing incredible things for other countries. If Simone Biles can be that great, imagine how many talents that are wasting away because people will not invest in gymnastics and train our children.\\\"  Video:  \\\"Na only the sports wey no need investment na im Nigeria dey\\\"  - Seun Kutipic.twitter.com/az8bxT2je3  - @ (@OneJoblessBoy)August 10, 2024    EndBadGovernance: Address demands of the youths - Musician Bongos Ikwue tells Nigerian Govt  God challenged me to curate only Christian playlist - DJ Cuppy  Fela's legacy debate: Wizkid's online clash with Seun Kuti divides Nigerian celebrities  'You have old woman as partner' - Seun Kuti hits Wizkid for insulting his wife  I am bigger than your father - Wizkid tells Seun Kuti  'Fela pioneered rap music' - Seun Kuti claims  'We can not be fighting over politicians' - Peter Okoye, Seun Kuti resolve feud  Seun Kuti denies using Wizkid's name for clout to revive career  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"